      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For the \"gold standard,\" think timeless elegance over fleeting trends, favoring classic tailoring and muted, luxurious tones. At galas, strict adherence to black tie or white tie is non-negotiable, and at business dinners, conservative, high-quality suiting is the safest bet. Table manners require mindful pacing—never rush, chew discreetly, and wait for the host to begin—while carrying yourself means maintaining composed body language, avoiding excessive gesturing, and speaking with measured thoughtfulness.",
      "source": "target",
