      "content": "In places like Lagos or Mumbai, while global business is present, local cultural norms regarding attire and formality often take precedence over strict Western standards; vibrant, high-quality local textiles can convey immense sophistication. In Kyoto, reverence for tradition means that even modern business attire must be handled with a deep sense of subtlety and restraint, valuing impeccable presentation over overt flashiness. The true global standard is knowing when to adapt your polished Western framework to honor the local cultural language of respect.",
